The paper deals with wireless networks and their communication models, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses algorithms for broadcasting and coloring, which are topics in Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of information theory in their analysis, which is a subfield of Theoretical Computer Science (cs.IT). The paper also deals with interference and transmission power, which are topics in Signal Processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and computational complexity, which are topics in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
